                        Telemedicine Systems Section

                                     TSS

  Telemedicine Systems Section (TSS)

   Chief: Kenneth M. Kempner, Chief

   The Telemedicine Systems Section (TSS) explores and develops image
   management and communication technologies in support of clinical image
   acquisition, transmission, and interpretation. It adapts and uses
   telemedicine and collaborative technologies to allow health care
   providers in remote locations to give real-time treatment to patients,
   and scientists to collaborate in research projects from geographically
   distributed sites. Research and development projects include:
     * TELESYNERGY(tm) Medical Consultation WorkStation System
     * Medical Image Display Systems
     * 3D Ultrasound Systems
     * High-speed Image Communication Networks
     * Medical Haptics
